WEBVTT

00:03.371 --> 00:06.605
Well, how do I look?

00:06.607 --> 00:08.507
Big day.
I'm going to see Alex.

00:08.509 --> 00:10.776
I'm, uh -- I'm a little nervous

00:10.778 --> 00:13.779
because she's been
pulling away lately.

00:13.781 --> 00:15.014
Calls don't get returned.

00:15.016 --> 00:18.050
I don't get asked
to visit as much.

00:18.052 --> 00:19.184
Maybe it's hitting me hard

00:19.186 --> 00:20.452
'cause I never went through that
with my dad.

00:20.454 --> 00:21.653
After my junior year,

00:21.655 --> 00:23.889
we -- we rode a tandem bike
across Mykonos.

00:23.891 --> 00:27.159
Come to think of it, there were
lots of fathers and sons there.

00:27.161 --> 00:28.394
Phil, sit.

00:28.396 --> 00:31.163
We need to talk about
the ducks.

00:31.165 --> 00:33.032
We hate the ducks.

00:34.502 --> 00:37.302
[ Duck quacks ]

00:37.304 --> 00:38.203
[ Duck quacks ]

00:38.205 --> 00:39.938
[ Duck quacking ]

00:42.643 --> 00:44.710
Again?
You have a problem.

00:45.813 --> 00:47.246
I'm hearing
a lot of negatives,

00:47.248 --> 00:49.348
but we're overlooking the fact
that feathers can now fetch.

00:49.350 --> 00:51.350
Honey, she pulled a wet
hot dog bun out of the sink,

00:51.352 --> 00:52.418
and you said,
"get the bun."

00:52.420 --> 00:53.719
That doesn't count
as fetching.

00:53.721 --> 00:55.687
Please tell me they're not gonna
live here forever.

00:55.689 --> 00:57.556
You're really not the one
to make that argument.

00:57.558 --> 00:58.690
Oh,
like you're not gonna

00:58.692 --> 01:00.492
die of natural causes
in that bunk bed upstairs.

01:00.494 --> 01:02.828
Look, we have provided them
with a good home.

01:02.830 --> 01:05.263
When they're ready,
they'll leave.

01:05.266 --> 01:06.365
Could be any day.

01:06.367 --> 01:07.833
Oh, and in the duck's defense,
Claire,

01:07.835 --> 01:09.835
you can't stick your leg
out of your robe at breakfast

01:09.837 --> 01:11.603
and then pretend
to hate the attention.

01:11.605 --> 01:14.873
Um...Why didn't you fight harder
about the ducks?

01:14.875 --> 01:16.442
You heard what he said.

01:16.444 --> 01:18.777
The ducks could leave
any day now.

01:18.779 --> 01:21.513
Yeah, or it could be
two months from now.

01:21.515 --> 01:23.515
Or <i> any</i> day now.

01:23.517 --> 01:24.616
Or a month and a half
fr--

01:24.618 --> 01:26.752
how are you
not getting this?

01:35.763 --> 01:37.429
♪♪

01:38.732 --> 01:41.233
Mitch called. He wants to know
when are you bringing

01:41.235 --> 01:43.102
the air mattress
for Lily's sleepover.

01:43.104 --> 01:45.604
You know, for a guy who refuses
to buy his own air mattresses,

01:45.606 --> 01:47.473
he's pretty particular
about when they arrive.

01:47.475 --> 01:49.041
No, no!
Don't eat my sauce.

01:49.043 --> 01:51.577
Then I won't have enough to sell
at the farmers' market.

01:51.579 --> 01:53.712
No.
Oh, geez.
Not the fat finger.

01:53.714 --> 01:55.747
You always do this
when I put on a few.

01:55.749 --> 01:56.882
I didn't say anything.

01:56.884 --> 01:58.117
It's not what you say.

01:58.119 --> 02:00.319
It's that damn lard
dipstick finger of yours.

02:00.321 --> 02:02.821
It disappeared
up to the second knuckle.

02:02.823 --> 02:04.156
Manny: Well, now that
that's over with,

02:04.158 --> 02:06.825
I can finally share my latest
football-related problem.

02:06.827 --> 02:08.560
Mitchell's right.
I should probably get a move on.

02:08.562 --> 02:10.596
The team left me out of
the end-of-the-season prank.

02:10.598 --> 02:12.164
You know,
that takes me back.

02:12.166 --> 02:15.334
We told the school board that
coach Davis was a communist.

02:15.336 --> 02:17.069
The man spent a weekend
[Chuckling] in jail.

02:17.071 --> 02:18.570
Simpler times.

02:18.572 --> 02:20.439
Well, that's better than
what these meatheads cooked up.

02:20.441 --> 02:21.907
They just parked
the principal's car

02:21.909 --> 02:23.408
in the middle
of the basketball court.

02:23.410 --> 02:24.643
[ Doorbell rings ]

02:24.645 --> 02:27.079
[ Laughs ]
That's not where cars go.

02:27.081 --> 02:29.448
Why didn't those meatballs
include you?

02:29.450 --> 02:31.316
They think
I'm a goody-two-shoes.

02:31.318 --> 02:32.184
Mm.

02:32.186 --> 02:33.018
I'm not.

02:33.020 --> 02:34.920
Mm.
My own mother?

02:34.922 --> 02:37.656
Ay, I'm just saying it wouldn't
kill you to break some rules.

02:37.658 --> 02:39.591
You're a minor.
Take advantage of it.

02:39.593 --> 02:41.026
I break the rules.

02:41.028 --> 02:43.929
I just prefer to be suave,
do it with panache and finesse.

02:43.931 --> 02:45.931
Ay, those are
American shampoos. I know.

02:45.933 --> 02:47.833
Y'all ready for this?

02:47.835 --> 02:49.701
I got our sauce into

02:49.703 --> 02:52.604
the granddaddy
of all holiday gift baskets.

02:52.606 --> 02:53.772
Which one?

02:53.774 --> 02:55.174
It's called granddaddy's
holiday gift baskets.

02:55.176 --> 02:56.441
Very exclusive.

02:56.443 --> 02:58.110
They want 150 jars...

02:58.112 --> 02:58.944
[ Gasps ] Yay!

02:58.946 --> 02:59.978
...by 6:00 tonight.

02:59.980 --> 03:02.381
No! It's too much sauce
for too little time.

03:02.383 --> 03:04.683
And anyways, I don't have
the key ingredient --

03:04.685 --> 03:06.051
the blood peppers.

03:06.053 --> 03:08.787
And my cousin can't send me more
from Colombia until next week.

03:08.789 --> 03:10.956
One spicy step
ahead of you.

03:10.958 --> 03:13.225
Enter
the serrano pepper!

03:13.227 --> 03:14.159
Chi-caw!

03:14.161 --> 03:15.294
No one
will know the difference.

03:15.296 --> 03:16.295
<i> I</i> will.

03:16.297 --> 03:18.463
This sauce
is part of my heritage.

03:18.465 --> 03:20.699
I cannot turn my back
on who I am.

03:20.701 --> 03:22.167
Didn't your hair
used to be darker?

03:22.169 --> 03:23.335
[ Gasps ]
I'm just saying

03:23.337 --> 03:27.139
this is a great opportunity
for our sauce.

03:27.141 --> 03:28.674
"Our sauce"?

03:28.676 --> 03:31.710
All of a sudden,
cam is calling it "our sauce"?

03:31.712 --> 03:33.745
I got that recipe
from my great aunt

03:33.747 --> 03:37.482
who got it from her mother
who stole it from a blind maid.

03:37.484 --> 03:38.984
How dare he.

03:38.986 --> 03:41.653
Fine. We'll just go get
some blood peppers.

03:41.655 --> 03:43.488
They're impossible to get.

03:43.490 --> 03:46.525
Unless you're willing
to break some rules.

03:46.527 --> 03:48.327
Why are we back on
your thing again?

03:48.329 --> 03:50.262
They just so happen
to grow blood peppers

03:50.264 --> 03:51.430
at the botanical gardens.

03:51.432 --> 03:52.331
Great. Let's go.

03:52.333 --> 03:53.665
You're adorable.

03:53.667 --> 03:56.001
We're talking rare flora
in a secure location.

03:56.003 --> 03:57.402
Okay, so,
then what do we do?

03:57.404 --> 03:59.771
First, apologize
for calling me a goody-goody,

03:59.773 --> 04:02.174
because I'm about
to lay out a plan so daring

04:02.176 --> 04:04.876
that the two of you may not have
the guts to follow it.

04:04.878 --> 04:05.877
Should I take my knife?

04:05.879 --> 04:07.412
I have my baseball bat
in my car.

04:07.414 --> 04:08.847
Okay,
we're stealing a pepper,

04:08.849 --> 04:10.449
not teaching
its family a lesson.

04:10.451 --> 04:11.683
Uh, okay.

04:11.685 --> 04:13.752
I noticed
a few of your professors

04:13.754 --> 04:15.520
in those
mouth-controlled wheelchairs.

04:15.522 --> 04:18.190
I think some of them are just
faking it to try and look cool.

04:18.192 --> 04:21.692
Domo arigato,
Mr. robotics lab!

04:21.695 --> 04:22.861
What?!

04:22.863 --> 04:24.896
Yeah. Come check out
these gloves. They're awesome.

04:24.898 --> 04:28.133
Any movement,
even the slightest motion,

04:28.135 --> 04:30.235
will be mirrored
by the robotic hands.

04:30.237 --> 04:32.537
Possible applications
are bomb defusement,

04:32.539 --> 04:35.807
nuclear reactor repair,
and remote neurosurgery.

04:35.809 --> 04:38.477
What has two thumbs
and any lady robot he wants?

04:38.479 --> 04:39.978
[ Robotic hands whirring ]
This guy.

04:39.980 --> 04:41.113
Dad, this isn't a toy.

04:41.115 --> 04:45.584
Hello,
my loyal robot subjects.

04:45.586 --> 04:46.485
Dad?

04:46.487 --> 04:47.586
Jazz hands!

04:47.588 --> 04:49.054
The other robots
are staring!

04:49.056 --> 04:51.657
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

04:51.659 --> 04:53.892
So, what's going on
at home?

04:53.894 --> 04:55.727
Well, Haley and Luke
aren't around much.

04:55.729 --> 04:58.063
Meanwhile, the ducks are awesome
and nobody gets it.

04:58.065 --> 05:00.432
You wouldn't believe this,
but one of them can fetch.

05:00.434 --> 05:01.566
Of course I believe it.

05:01.568 --> 05:02.734
One of my professors

05:02.736 --> 05:04.903
taught a chimpanzee
how to play the saxophone.

05:04.905 --> 05:07.072
We all think he's great,
but he only plays jazz,

05:07.074 --> 05:08.240
so there's no way to tell.

05:08.242 --> 05:10.342
Oh.
Tell me about these fellas.

05:10.344 --> 05:12.577
Well, this one's being developed
for the military.

05:12.579 --> 05:13.779
Really? Wow.
Mm-hmm.

05:13.781 --> 05:15.447
What about this adorable guy?
Hello, switch.

05:15.449 --> 05:16.648
Oh, no!
Dad, don't press that.

05:16.650 --> 05:18.150
Oh, he's just
going for a little walk.

05:18.152 --> 05:19.751
Why would you do that?!
The master switch!

05:19.753 --> 05:20.819
The what?

05:22.589 --> 05:23.655
No, no, no!

05:23.657 --> 05:24.923
Oh, my God.

05:24.925 --> 05:25.957
It's happening!

05:25.959 --> 05:27.125
They're rising up!

05:27.127 --> 05:28.527
Turn off!

05:28.529 --> 05:29.861
I command you to turn off!

05:29.863 --> 05:30.829
It's not working!

05:30.831 --> 05:31.763
I'm on your side!

05:31.765 --> 05:32.931
Why would you do that?!

05:32.933 --> 05:34.599
I don't know
what I was thinking!

05:34.601 --> 05:35.867
I'm so sorry.

05:35.869 --> 05:37.502
[ Sighs ]

05:39.640 --> 05:43.041
Great. Now the captain
of the football team hates me.

05:48.682 --> 05:49.848
Okay, follow my plan
to the letter,

05:49.850 --> 05:51.283
and in 10 minutes,
we'll have peppers in hand.

05:51.285 --> 05:52.351
Manny: It's Saturday.

05:52.353 --> 05:54.319
William will be working
the rose garden.

05:54.321 --> 05:55.954
Fortunately,
he'll be distracted.

05:55.956 --> 05:57.956
Right now, the aphids
have the upper hand.

05:57.958 --> 05:59.958
Cam, when you reach
the stream,

05:59.960 --> 06:03.028
follow it South southeast
to the hummingbird exhibit.

06:03.030 --> 06:04.396
Interact with no one.

06:04.398 --> 06:06.298
Excuse me.
Could you take this for us?

06:06.300 --> 06:08.133
Oh, guess
I have a second.

06:08.135 --> 06:09.034
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

06:09.036 --> 06:10.969
Oops.
Took a picture of myself.

06:10.971 --> 06:12.037
[ Chuckles ]

06:12.039 --> 06:14.639
Oh, and now
it's your wallpaper. Uh...

06:14.641 --> 06:17.876
Manny: Mom, to avoid detection,
take a circuitous route

06:17.878 --> 06:20.679
to the Edmund and Miriam
rabinowitz pepper patch.

06:20.681 --> 06:22.547
Hey!

06:22.549 --> 06:25.717
Take me
to the blood peppers.

06:25.719 --> 06:28.820
I'll re-route
the senior citizens' tour...

06:28.822 --> 06:31.390
You've already been this way.
You loved it.

06:31.392 --> 06:34.593
...so they're not around
when you arrive at the peppers.

06:34.595 --> 06:37.329
Go away, boy.

06:37.331 --> 06:40.232
Manny: Be on alert.
There may be added security.

06:44.104 --> 06:45.370
Wow.
How exhilarating.

06:45.372 --> 06:47.606
I didn't know there was
a caper in our sauce.

06:47.608 --> 06:49.074
[ Chuckles ]
How could you?

06:49.076 --> 06:51.176
It's not your recipe.

06:51.178 --> 06:52.210
[ Laughter ]

06:52.212 --> 06:53.912
Hey, girls.
How about a snack?

06:53.914 --> 06:55.580
[ All yelling ]

06:55.582 --> 06:57.048
[ Chuckles ]

06:57.050 --> 06:59.618
I'm hosting a sleepover for
lily's vietnamese dance troupe.

06:59.620 --> 07:01.887
We want her to be more in touch
with her heritage,

07:01.889 --> 07:04.790
but breaking the ice
with the other parents
has been a little tough.

07:04.792 --> 07:06.958
Cam and I are
the only white parents,

07:06.960 --> 07:08.693
the only gay parents,

07:08.695 --> 07:10.896
the only parents
that find us funny.

07:10.898 --> 07:14.566
Hi. Come on in,
Patricia, Ms. tran.

07:14.568 --> 07:16.201
The girls
are in lily's room.

07:16.203 --> 07:17.736
Oh, this is
a fun coincidence.

07:17.738 --> 07:20.605
We actually had a couple trans
over for dinner last ni--

07:21.875 --> 07:23.208
the hardest nut to crack

07:23.210 --> 07:25.377
has been
little Patricia tran's mother.

07:25.379 --> 07:28.046
I didn't try her homemade pho
at a potluck once,

07:28.048 --> 07:30.048
and now she doesn't like me.

07:30.050 --> 07:33.118
You could say it was a little
bit of a pho pa.
[Faux pas]

07:33.120 --> 07:34.152
Hello.

07:34.154 --> 07:35.754
Your husband?
My dad.

07:35.756 --> 07:37.889
And I prefer brunettes,
without beards.

07:37.891 --> 07:39.324
I like women.

07:39.326 --> 07:42.127
I'll bring Patricia's medicine
over later.

07:43.564 --> 07:44.830
My purse.

07:44.832 --> 07:46.131
Mm-hmm.

07:46.133 --> 07:47.098
She seems nice.

07:47.100 --> 07:48.500
Yeah.
[ Indistinct chatter, laughter ]

07:48.502 --> 07:49.568
Hey, grandpa!

07:49.570 --> 07:50.735
Hi, sweetheart!

07:50.737 --> 07:52.304
Little tip --
you might want the girls

07:52.306 --> 07:54.406
to blow up these air mattresses,
tire them out a little bit.

07:54.408 --> 07:56.141
Oh, I'm not trying
to tire them out.

07:56.143 --> 07:57.309
No.
I'm the fun dad, okay?

07:57.311 --> 07:58.743
I want them
to have a good time.

07:58.745 --> 07:59.678
That's a rookie mistake.

07:59.680 --> 08:00.979
When you are Claire
were kids,

08:00.981 --> 08:02.581
I was the sleepover champ,
undefeated.

08:02.583 --> 08:04.816
There was never a kid that was
awake later than 7:30.

08:04.818 --> 08:06.184
Oh, no.
I remember my 10th birthday.

08:06.186 --> 08:08.019
You let us wash your car,
and then we carried

08:08.021 --> 08:09.454
the grandfather clock
to the dump.

08:09.456 --> 08:11.189
Yeah, sun exposure
plays a big part.

08:11.191 --> 08:12.457
What's this stuff?

08:12.459 --> 08:14.960
Uh, mom, uh, mailed me a bunch
of stuff from her garage.

08:14.962 --> 08:17.496
She thought I might like a vcr
and a bunch of old tapes.

08:17.498 --> 08:19.297
Sweet of dede
to mail you her garbage.

08:19.299 --> 08:21.867
"Jane Fonda complete workouts,"
"it's not you, it's him,"

08:21.869 --> 08:23.034
"cooking with chocolate."

08:23.036 --> 08:24.703
Pretty much the arc
of our whole marriage.

08:24.705 --> 08:27.272
Listen, if you're smart,

08:27.274 --> 08:29.274
you'll let the girls walk
this stuff down to goodwill.

08:29.276 --> 08:31.543
Or I could provide a fun,
entertaining evening

08:31.545 --> 08:34.179
that will only enrich
my daughter's childhood.

08:34.181 --> 08:36.448
Daddy, will you judge
our screaming contest?

08:36.450 --> 08:38.350
Of course he will!
Hit it, girls!

08:38.352 --> 08:39.951
[ Girls screaming ]

08:39.953 --> 08:43.288
Okay! You won. You all won.
It's a tie.

08:43.289 --> 08:47.225
Oh, honey, I am so sorry about
what happened in there.

08:47.227 --> 08:49.461
Don't worry about me,
but, you know,

08:49.463 --> 08:52.063
those robots are programmed
to hold a grudge.

08:52.065 --> 08:53.798
Not how I wanted
this to go.

08:53.800 --> 08:56.301
Probably gonna be a while before
I get invited back here, huh?

08:56.303 --> 08:58.537
Dad, it's okay.

08:58.539 --> 09:00.705
You're probably going to be
seeing me a lot more,

09:00.707 --> 09:02.874
considering I want
to move back home

09:02.876 --> 09:05.143
and commute to school
next semester.

09:05.145 --> 09:06.478
Wow. Really?

09:06.480 --> 09:09.214
Yeah.
It's only a half-hour drive.

09:09.216 --> 09:10.382
Are you mad?

09:10.384 --> 09:12.384
Mad? Are you kidding me?
I'm thrilled.

09:12.386 --> 09:13.985
You know
how much I miss you.

09:13.987 --> 09:16.321
We could have our own robot lab
in the garage.

09:16.323 --> 09:17.989
How much
could that possibly cost?

09:17.991 --> 09:19.157
Well [Chuckles]

09:19.159 --> 09:22.327
But, uh -- but why?
Did something happen?

09:22.329 --> 09:24.563
No, it's just --

09:24.565 --> 09:27.265
ugh, the people here
are all so immature.

09:27.267 --> 09:29.000
They are always
banging on your door

09:29.002 --> 09:31.903
with a beaker full
of margaritas, and...

09:31.905 --> 09:33.405
The nerd noise
is deafening.

09:33.407 --> 09:35.507
Did you bring those
noise-canceling headphones

09:35.509 --> 09:36.441
I asked mom for?

09:36.443 --> 09:38.176
Oh, I am so sorry.
I forgot.

09:38.178 --> 09:40.779
Sometimes my brain cancels out
your mom's noise.

09:40.781 --> 09:41.746
[ Chuckles ]

09:41.748 --> 09:43.181
I'll, uh --
I'll pick some up

09:43.183 --> 09:45.350
while you're in class
and then drop them by the dorm.

09:45.352 --> 09:46.785
Thanks.

09:46.787 --> 09:47.852
Excuse me.

09:47.854 --> 09:49.588
Cannon ball tonight.
Don't miss it.

09:49.590 --> 09:51.556
Oh, no, no.
Thanks.

09:51.558 --> 09:52.691
What's that about?

09:52.693 --> 09:54.426
Oh, it's just some
stupid tradition where,

09:54.428 --> 09:55.527
at the end
of the semester,

09:55.529 --> 09:57.095
all the freshmen jump off
a high dive

09:57.097 --> 09:58.797
in cheesy prom dresses.

09:58.799 --> 10:00.131
Oh, that could be fun.

10:00.133 --> 10:01.299
It definitely won't be.

10:01.301 --> 10:03.234
Well, maybe if you
give it a chance...

10:03.236 --> 10:04.269
No.
You know what, dad?

10:04.271 --> 10:05.537
I-I-I did.

10:05.539 --> 10:07.539
I've -- I've already been
to like 10 parties,

10:07.541 --> 10:08.640
and they're all lame.

10:08.642 --> 10:10.909
Everyone just talks
to their own dorm mate.

10:10.911 --> 10:13.311
Sweetie, sometimes it takes
a while to warm up to people.

10:13.313 --> 10:15.547
What is this about?
Do you not want me to come home?

10:15.549 --> 10:16.815
Is that what this is?

10:16.817 --> 10:20.085
Because, fine, I'll just
go get an apartment off campus.

10:20.087 --> 10:21.386
Alex, don't get mad.

10:21.388 --> 10:22.387
Well, I <i> am</i> mad.

10:22.389 --> 10:23.655
Because I'm actually
smart enough

10:23.657 --> 10:25.390
to know what's working for me
and what isn't,

10:25.392 --> 10:28.493
and this isn't.

10:28.495 --> 10:29.794
I have to go to class.

10:30.897 --> 10:32.797
Guy: Heads up! Watch out!

10:34.468 --> 10:37.068
How'd he do that?

10:37.070 --> 10:38.303
Mitchell?

10:38.305 --> 10:41.072
Lily:
In the kitchen, grandpa!

10:41.074 --> 10:43.074
Vietnamese girls
and a man in makeup.

10:43.076 --> 10:44.943
When does Bob hope
take the stage?

10:44.945 --> 10:46.011
Delightful.

10:46.013 --> 10:48.079
You're good to go
on the air mattresses.

10:48.081 --> 10:50.815
Good luck
with the sleepover.

10:52.586 --> 10:53.585
Yes, ma'am?

10:53.587 --> 10:55.320
I don't want to be
the fun dad anymore.

10:55.322 --> 10:57.455
I need to knock
these girls out quick.

10:57.457 --> 10:58.657
Teach me.

10:58.659 --> 11:01.760
♪♪

11:01.762 --> 11:04.095
Let's go, ladies!
Reach to the sky!

11:04.097 --> 11:05.930
Mitchell: How are you better
at this than Jane Fonda?

11:05.932 --> 11:06.998
Mitchell, you can't talk

11:07.000 --> 11:08.633
and feel the burn
at the same time.

11:08.635 --> 11:10.669
Donkey-kick
like you mean it, Jennifer.

11:10.671 --> 11:13.204
I'm just curious, because this
tape was on its way to goodwill,

11:13.206 --> 11:15.340
and all of a sudden, you pulled
it out of your back pocket.

11:15.342 --> 11:17.108
I put on a couple
of extra pounds,

11:17.110 --> 11:19.377
and Jane got me out of a similar
situation in the '80s.

11:19.379 --> 11:21.379
Please tell me you were
wearing leg warmers.

11:21.381 --> 11:22.781
Leave me alone.
Oh.

11:22.783 --> 11:25.316
We got this, girls.
March it out.

11:25.318 --> 11:27.619
Well, for whatever it's worth,
dad, I didn't notice.

11:27.621 --> 11:28.853
Gloria did.

11:28.855 --> 11:31.289
She did that little poke thing
to my spare tire.

11:31.291 --> 11:33.058
Lily, keep the beat.

11:33.060 --> 11:35.460
I hate to admit it, but it
bugged the hell out of me.

11:35.462 --> 11:38.463
Kim-ly, we're punching
and we're stepping.

11:38.465 --> 11:40.031
Care to join us?

11:40.033 --> 11:42.300
So, I figured
I'd do this workout

11:42.302 --> 11:43.902
every damn day
of the week

11:43.904 --> 11:46.838
until I was nothing
but abs, buns, and thighs.

11:46.840 --> 11:48.707
Work your glutes,
Tiffany!

11:48.709 --> 11:50.208
This is
your problem area.

11:50.210 --> 11:52.877
Okay, dad, no offense,
but I've been listening

11:52.879 --> 11:55.413
to you whine about gaining
and losing the same 10 pounds

11:55.415 --> 11:56.881
since, at age 60,
you married

11:56.883 --> 11:58.717
the most beautiful woman
in the world.

11:58.719 --> 12:01.252
And while I appreciate what
might be the rich-white-mannest

12:01.254 --> 12:02.821
of rich-white-man
problems,

12:02.823 --> 12:05.657
this tape is only energizing
these little girls.

12:05.659 --> 12:06.658
This is boring.

12:06.660 --> 12:08.259
Let's go and build a fort
in my room.

12:08.261 --> 12:09.327
Girl: Okay.

12:09.329 --> 12:10.595
So, what?
You're just gonna give up?

12:10.597 --> 12:12.263
You got to know
when to surrender.

12:12.265 --> 12:13.498
No, sir.

12:13.500 --> 12:15.600
I'm not losing to the vietnamese
twice in a lifetime.

12:15.602 --> 12:16.835
Get up.

12:16.837 --> 12:18.436
No man left behind.
Okay.

12:18.438 --> 12:21.606
Look at this golf course.
It's a beautiful home for ducks.

12:21.608 --> 12:23.875
Okay, now, who's gonna
help me

12:23.877 --> 12:26.177
set these little suckers free,
huh?

12:26.179 --> 12:27.178
You do it.
I'm good.

12:27.180 --> 12:28.613
Oh, come on.
[ Ducks quacking ]

12:28.615 --> 12:30.548
We all hate the ducks.
We all want them gone.

12:30.550 --> 12:32.350
Why do I have to be
the bad guy?

12:32.352 --> 12:33.685
I don't know.
Why am I the pretty one?

12:33.687 --> 12:34.619
We all have our thing.

12:34.621 --> 12:36.955
Fine. Fine.
I'll do it.

12:36.957 --> 12:38.189
Okay.

12:38.191 --> 12:40.725
Get on out there. There you go.
You're free. Okay.

12:40.727 --> 12:43.128
Why aren't they
going anywhere?

12:43.130 --> 12:45.764
Well, miss thing over there is
still getting herself ready.

12:45.766 --> 12:47.065
I swear
she spent all morning

12:47.067 --> 12:49.100
looking at her reflection
in the water bowl.

12:49.102 --> 12:50.935
[ Chuckles ]
How about that weirdo?

12:50.937 --> 12:53.471
Did you see when
he got his bill stuck
in his cage yesterday?

12:53.473 --> 12:54.806
What a sweet little dope.
[ Chuckles ]

12:54.808 --> 12:57.142
I know. He's lucky
his sister is so smart.

12:57.144 --> 12:59.711
You know, she figured out
how to unlatch the cage

12:59.713 --> 13:00.812
and set him free.

13:00.814 --> 13:02.881
[ Chuckles ]

13:02.883 --> 13:04.883
Oh, my God.

13:04.885 --> 13:07.919
Do you guys see
what's happening?

13:07.921 --> 13:09.120
No.
Of course you don't.

13:09.122 --> 13:11.422
The reason why your dad is
so attached to these ducks

13:11.424 --> 13:13.892
is they remind him
of you guys.

13:13.894 --> 13:15.059
We got to get them home.

13:15.061 --> 13:16.461
They're gone.

13:16.463 --> 13:18.563
Oh, my God.

13:18.565 --> 13:20.398
Where are they?

13:20.400 --> 13:22.066
Oh, God.

13:22.068 --> 13:23.902
What the hell?

13:23.904 --> 13:25.804
Does everyone get rid
of their ducks here?

13:25.806 --> 13:26.671
[ Ducks quacking ]

13:31.745 --> 13:33.344
[ Ducks quaking ]
Can't we just
pick any three?

13:33.346 --> 13:34.979
Mnh-mnh. Your father will know
immediately.

13:34.981 --> 13:37.515
Look. I think that might be
the dumb Luke duck.

13:37.517 --> 13:39.984
The one entertaining the others?
[ Chuckles ]

13:39.986 --> 13:42.120
His head is caught
in the fritos bag.

13:42.122 --> 13:44.088
Hey. Isn't that your duck?
Where?

13:44.090 --> 13:47.258
The one pushing oats around with
its beak, pretending to eat.

13:47.260 --> 13:48.960
All right. That's it.
Go get your ducks. Go.

13:48.962 --> 13:50.428
What? No.
It is filthy and filmy.

13:50.430 --> 13:52.030
And that's before
Luke even gets in it.

13:52.032 --> 13:53.298
What's the point
in getting two ducks

13:53.300 --> 13:54.532
if we don't have
the third one?

13:54.534 --> 13:55.934
And how are we supposed to
find the Alex duck?

13:55.936 --> 13:58.269
Wait until new year's Eve
and see which one stays home?

13:58.271 --> 13:59.604
No. No. You're right.

13:59.606 --> 14:01.706
We are not going home
without all three ducks.

14:01.708 --> 14:05.476
Hang on.
Let's see if your dad was right.

14:05.478 --> 14:06.377
Feather.

14:06.379 --> 14:09.113
Feather. Fetch.

14:09.115 --> 14:11.716
[ Duck quacks ]

14:11.718 --> 14:13.618
No way.

14:13.620 --> 14:15.119
Don't just stand there.
Get your ducks.

14:15.121 --> 14:17.322
I just spent a week's salary
on these shoes.

14:17.324 --> 14:19.524
I'm not -- oh, look at
those big brown eyes.

14:19.526 --> 14:20.859
They take up half her face!

14:20.861 --> 14:22.460
I'm coming, princess!

14:22.462 --> 14:23.895
Aah!

14:24.564 --> 14:25.697
Pardon me.

14:25.699 --> 14:28.199
Sorry. Have fun.

14:31.338 --> 14:35.673
[ Robotic voice ]
What's the most dangerous type
of uranium cake?

14:35.675 --> 14:36.975
Yellow!

14:36.977 --> 14:38.409
Hey.

14:38.411 --> 14:40.378
What's going on?

14:40.380 --> 14:42.814
Um, I found this inhaler.
Do you know whose it is?

14:42.816 --> 14:44.916
There's only six people here
who don't use those.

14:44.918 --> 14:46.751
They throw them in the air
at graduation.

14:46.753 --> 14:48.753
All right.

14:48.755 --> 14:50.188
Hey, did you bring
those headphones?

14:50.190 --> 14:51.356
Yeah. Right here.

14:51.358 --> 14:53.057
Thanks.

14:53.059 --> 14:55.260
[ Clears throat ]

14:55.262 --> 14:57.662
Hey, honey.

14:57.664 --> 14:59.831
I'm sorry about earlier.

14:59.833 --> 15:02.901
I think maybe being on
a college campus took me back,

15:02.903 --> 15:08.006
and some of my own first-year
insecurities bubbled up.

15:08.008 --> 15:10.909
I didn't know anybody,
and no matter how hard I tried,

15:10.911 --> 15:12.443
I was always on the outside.

15:12.445 --> 15:15.580
And then suddenly, one day,
something clicked and I was in.

15:15.582 --> 15:17.849
I mean, you never know.

15:17.851 --> 15:19.550
I mean, just because
that happened to you,

15:19.552 --> 15:21.185
doesn't mean that's --
no, no, no, no, no.

15:21.187 --> 15:22.687
That's -- that's my point.

15:22.689 --> 15:25.690
My story isn't your story.

15:25.692 --> 15:27.425
As intimidating
as this place may be,

15:27.427 --> 15:30.695
I've never seen you walk away
from a challenge.

15:30.697 --> 15:32.730
If you tell me you've given it
your best shot,

15:32.732 --> 15:35.133
then I know you have.

15:35.135 --> 15:36.567
So don't be mad at me,
okay?

15:36.569 --> 15:38.569
I'm not mad.

15:38.571 --> 15:40.738
All right, kiddo.

15:40.740 --> 15:43.408
Your mom and I will be back
next week to pack you up.

15:43.410 --> 15:44.375
I love you.

15:44.377 --> 15:45.443
I love you, too.

15:47.047 --> 15:50.014
Bye.
Bye.

16:00.760 --> 16:02.727
[ Chuckles ]

16:02.729 --> 16:06.297
Okay. Granddaddy's truck's
gonna be here in 84 minutes.

16:06.299 --> 16:08.900
So, we're tightening,
we're stirring, we're chopping.

16:08.902 --> 16:09.834
Bottle it up!

16:09.836 --> 16:11.169
I can't.
I'm just too excited.

16:11.171 --> 16:13.571
Oh, oh, you mean the sauce
in the -- got it. Yes.

16:15.075 --> 16:16.975
Cam...

16:16.977 --> 16:18.109
What is this?
Oh, my gosh.

16:18.111 --> 16:19.644
You weren't supposed
to see these yet.

16:19.646 --> 16:23.281
This is just a potential label
idea that I-I had mocked up.

16:23.283 --> 16:24.082
So...

16:24.084 --> 16:25.316
But I am not even on it.

16:25.318 --> 16:26.784
No, you are.
Yes, you are.

16:26.786 --> 16:29.420
See? You're the silhouette right
here by the nutritional facts.

16:29.422 --> 16:31.089
That way,
people are looking at you

16:31.091 --> 16:32.757
and not the toxic amount
of sodium.

16:32.759 --> 16:33.925
I have others, too.

16:33.927 --> 16:35.927
You know, I have one of us
on a pepper rocket

16:35.929 --> 16:37.095
on our way
to flavor city.

16:37.097 --> 16:38.796
You're in front of me,
and it's cute.

16:38.798 --> 16:41.332
You know what? I don't think
this partnership is working.

16:42.702 --> 16:43.968
What are you saying?

16:43.970 --> 16:45.103
What am I saying?

16:45.105 --> 16:46.771
This is family's sauce,

16:46.773 --> 16:49.140
and you have already tried
to change the recipe.

16:49.142 --> 16:52.477
You took a huge order
without even asking me.

16:52.479 --> 16:53.845
And now this?

16:53.847 --> 16:58.449
If I am going to flavor city,
I am going by myself.

17:01.121 --> 17:02.653
You're breaking up
with me?

17:02.655 --> 17:04.288
When I first started dating cam,

17:04.290 --> 17:06.290
his ex-boyfriend
gave me a heads up.

17:06.291 --> 17:08.126
He said, "cam's a great guy,

17:08.127 --> 17:10.294
but I hope you never have to
break up with him."

17:10.296 --> 17:11.996
And I said,
"why? Does he get angry,

17:11.998 --> 17:14.132
weepy, jealous, despondent?"

17:14.134 --> 17:16.134
He said, "yes."

17:16.136 --> 17:17.902
<i> You're</i> breaking up
with <i> me?</i>

17:17.904 --> 17:19.871
This business
was <i> my</i> idea.

17:19.873 --> 17:21.705
I got you into
the farmers' market.

17:21.708 --> 17:23.674
I got you into
those baskets.

17:23.675 --> 17:26.511
You were nothing but a housewife
when I found you.

17:26.512 --> 17:28.512
I didn't mean that.
I've always admired you.

17:28.515 --> 17:30.314
Being a housewife is
the hardest job on the planet.

17:30.316 --> 17:31.682
You're never not at work.

17:31.684 --> 17:33.484
[ Crying ] It's just --
how did we get to this place?

17:33.486 --> 17:34.886
Unless...

17:34.888 --> 17:36.821
There's someone else,
isn't there?

17:36.823 --> 17:39.223
Oh, how could I be
so blind?

17:39.225 --> 17:41.659
Let me guess -- somebody
with more experience?

17:41.661 --> 17:44.262
Somebody Colombian?

17:44.264 --> 17:46.898
Well,
you're no picnic, either.

17:46.900 --> 17:49.200
So, who is it?

17:49.202 --> 17:51.035
Hmm?

17:51.037 --> 17:52.236
Say something!

17:53.273 --> 17:55.573
I've seen my mom break up
with a lot of guys.

17:55.575 --> 17:58.276
She has this weird power
to get them to do all the work.

17:58.278 --> 17:59.577
One minute, they're a mess.

17:59.579 --> 18:01.045
The next, they're thanking her

18:01.047 --> 18:02.780
for the best year
of their lives.

18:02.782 --> 18:04.949
The last guy helped us
move into Jay's house.

18:04.951 --> 18:06.350
You knew.

18:06.352 --> 18:09.287
You knew I needed the motivation
to create my own sauce.

18:09.289 --> 18:10.855
You knew all along.

18:10.857 --> 18:12.423
You're welcome, cam.
And don't worry.

18:12.425 --> 18:14.425
I know that one day,
you're gonna have your sauce

18:14.427 --> 18:16.394
in granddaddy's basket.

18:16.396 --> 18:17.962
Well,
that paints a picture.

18:17.964 --> 18:20.131
Now, see, there's lots of stuff
here to tire the kids out.

18:20.133 --> 18:22.967
Look -- bricks for carrying,
shovels for digging.

18:22.969 --> 18:24.202
Shovels.
When did we get shovels?

18:24.204 --> 18:25.470
Okay, well,
whatever you're doing,

18:25.472 --> 18:26.471
can you do it someplace else?

18:26.473 --> 18:27.805
I'm helping Gloria bottle
her sauce,

18:27.807 --> 18:28.940
and we're
running out of time.

18:28.942 --> 18:30.374
Ay, cam.
I think it's too late.

18:30.376 --> 18:32.076
I don't think we have
enough time to finish.

18:32.078 --> 18:33.578
You might.

18:33.580 --> 18:35.780
Oh, Ms. tran.
Is that Patricia's medicine?

18:35.782 --> 18:38.583
Jay:
Pick up the pace, ladies!

18:38.585 --> 18:40.718
Come on! We've only got
20 minutes!

18:40.720 --> 18:43.154
Trust me. This is
slightly better than it looks.

18:43.156 --> 18:44.889
My fingers hurt.

18:44.891 --> 18:47.792
Hey, honey, what did I say
about talking on the line?

18:51.397 --> 18:53.064
Okay. Let's just get these ducks
back into the garage

18:53.066 --> 18:54.398
as fast as we can,
and please be quiet.

18:54.400 --> 18:55.933
I don't want
your father to hear us.
Hello.

18:55.935 --> 18:57.268
Oh, uh...

18:57.270 --> 19:01.939
I got home early and noticed
the six of you had...Ducked out.

19:01.941 --> 19:03.808
Well, we know how much
you love the ducks,

19:03.810 --> 19:05.776
and -- and we wanted
to play with them, too.

19:05.778 --> 19:08.112
And we --
and what, Claire?

19:08.114 --> 19:09.747
The craziest thing
happened?

19:09.749 --> 19:12.250
You turned a hard corner,
the cage banged open,

19:12.252 --> 19:14.185
one of them hit
the sunroof button,

19:14.187 --> 19:17.088
and out they flew, leaving us
with nothing but an empty --

19:17.090 --> 19:19.090
I interrupted you.
Go on.
[ Ducks quaking ]

19:19.092 --> 19:21.592
We have not always
loved the ducks, Phil,

19:21.594 --> 19:23.628
but I think
we're starting to get it.

19:23.630 --> 19:26.430
Yeah. We want them to stay.
We know why you love them.

19:26.432 --> 19:27.598
Thank you.

19:27.600 --> 19:29.634
I always knew it was
only a matter of time

19:29.636 --> 19:31.936
before these little scamps
waddled into your hearts

19:31.938 --> 19:34.005
just like they did mine.

19:34.007 --> 19:36.174
Now, come on. Help me throw them
out the window.

19:37.944 --> 19:39.210
Dad, what are you doing?

19:39.212 --> 19:42.280
It is time for them to go.

19:42.282 --> 19:44.148
But, honey, are you sure
they can even fly?

19:44.150 --> 19:46.317
According to the Internet,
they were ready a month ago.

19:46.319 --> 19:48.286
At breakfast, you were
giving them shoulder rubs.

19:48.288 --> 19:49.554
What happened?

19:49.556 --> 19:51.522
I realized today that I may
have been holding them back

19:51.524 --> 19:53.624
because that was fun
for me.

19:53.626 --> 19:58.296
But in the end, you got to let
them spread their wings, right?

19:58.298 --> 20:00.131
♪♪

20:00.133 --> 20:02.800
Girl #1: Whoo! Let's go!
Girl #2: All right, Alex!

20:02.802 --> 20:06.404
[ Cheers and applause ]

20:06.406 --> 20:08.472
All right, guys.
Let's do this.

20:08.474 --> 20:10.975
One, two...

20:10.977 --> 20:13.077
Come visit us!

20:14.647 --> 20:16.747
Make good choices!

20:16.749 --> 20:19.250
[ Sighs ]
In many ways,
<i> you</i> fetched <i> me!</i>

20:21.321 --> 20:24.922
♪♪

20:24.924 --> 20:27.658
[ Cheers and applause ]

20:34.334 --> 20:37.001
[ Clears throat ]
You caught me.

20:37.003 --> 20:38.669
I know
they're not coming back.

20:38.671 --> 20:41.505
Mm, sometimes they do.

20:42.775 --> 20:45.576
Hello?

20:45.578 --> 20:47.278
Hey, Alex.

20:47.280 --> 20:50.548
What's going on,
sweetheart?

20:50.550 --> 20:51.616
Yeah?

20:56.089 --> 20:58.356
"Once the lower spring hinge
is secured,

20:58.358 --> 21:01.759
you can then attach
the closet door."

21:05.198 --> 21:07.465
They're all sleeping, Mitch.

21:07.467 --> 21:09.734
Not bad.

21:09.736 --> 21:13.304
7:45. Room for improvement.

21:14.974 --> 21:17.875
Well, it looks like
I'm still undefeated.
